Name: @PACKAGE@
Version: @VERSION@
Release: 1
Group: Development/Libraries
Vendor: Tom Gilbert <tom@linuxbrit.co.uk>
Packager: Janus N. Tøndering <janus@bananus.dk>
Url: http://www.linuxbrit.co.uk/
Source: %{name}-%{version}.tar.gz
License: OpenSource
Summary: Utility library wrapping imlib2 and more

BuildRoot: /tmp/%{name}-build
Requires: imlib2 >= 1.0.0
BuildRequires: imlib2-devel

%package devel
Group: Development/Libraries
Requires: %{name} = %{version}
Summary: Development libraries and headers

%description
giblib is a utility library used by many of the applications I 
write. It incorporates doubly linked lists, some string functions, 
and a wrapper for imlib2. The wrapper does two things. It gives 
you access to fontstyles, which can be loaded from files, saved 
to files or defined dynamically through the API. It also, and 
more importantly, wraps imlib2's context API changing

%description devel


